    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix buffer overflow in nfapi_p7_deallocate function\n\n### Summary\nThe `nfapi_p7_deallocate` function in the nFAPI library was incorrectly trying to return values from void functions (`free()` and user-provided deallocate callbacks). This caused undefined behavior that could lead to buffer overflow conditions when memory was not properly deallocated.\n\nThis fix corrects the function by removing the erroneous return statements, ensuring proper void function calls for memory deallocation.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: Fixed `nfapi_p7_deallocate` function to properly call deallocation functions without returning their void return values.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure OAI with custom memory management callbacks in `nfapi_p7_codec_config_t`\n2. Process P7 messages that trigger memory allocation/deallocation\n3. Observe potential memory corruption or segmentation fault due to improper deallocation handling\n\nThe issue manifests as memory corruption during deallocation operations, particularly when using custom allocators.\n"
}